## Usage

Import the JS:
```js
import "@hyperkit/components/calendar";
```

Tags:
```html
<hyperkit-calendar>...</hyperkit-calendar>
```

### Options

{% table %}
* Attribute
* Value
* 
---
* `for`
* The name of a corresponding `<input />` which will receive the value selected (and update the calendar if it's edited manually).
---
* `min-date`
* ISO Date String (ie. 2024-10-13)
* Specifies a minimum date - earlier dates will be disabled
---
* `max-date`
* ISO Date String (ie. 2024-10-13)
* Specifies a maximum date - earlier dates will be disabled
---
* `future-only`
* Boolean (omit for false)
* Only allows selecting future dates
---
* `past-only`
* Boolean (omit for false)
* Only allows selecting past dates
---
{% /table %}

### Children

```html
<hyperkit-calendar>
	<template>
		<hk-previous-month />
		<hk-current-month />
		<hk-next-month />
		<hk-days-list />
		<hk-day-number />
	</template>
</hyperkit-calendar>
```

#### Why `<template>...</template>`?
* The calendar relies on javascript to function - so we don't want to display any artefects when JS isn't available
* Nesting the markup inside a `<template />` achieves this

#### `<hk-previous-month />` and `<hk-next-month />`
* Provide navigation between months
* Are replaced with `<button />`s at invocation
* Should be treated as a `<button />`

#### `<hk-current-month />`
* Placeholder for the name of the current month
* Should be treated as a `<div />`

#### `<hk-days-list />`
* Will receive the list of day numbers for the current month, as clickable buttons for selection
* Should be treated as a `<div />`

#### `<hk-day-number />`
* Template for the day numbers
* Is replaced with a `<button />` when rendered into the days list
* Should be treated as a `<button />`


## Examples

### A full, styled calendar

